GET FEDORA INSTALLED
    Go to getfedora.org
    Prepare USB with netinstall server
    In installation process, pick "minimal" setup.

FIRST STEPS
    1) BIOS boot order
	Connect SSD drive and give it priority over eMMC storage.
    1) update (shouldn't be needed after net install)
        # dnf update
    2) get basic software
        # dnf install nano mc tree openssh wget bash-completion tar gcc gdb git
    3) enable and start sshd (should be already enabled and running)
        # systemctl status sshd
        # systemctl enable sshd && systemctl start sshd
    4) get IP address
        # ip a
	    -> enp2s0 -> inet
    5) connect via ssh (trick to find the device connected to the same LAN)
        for i in {1..255}; do ssh -o ConnectTimeout=2 root@192.168.0.$i; done
    6) enable wi-fi
        # dnf install NetworkManager-wifi
        # systemctl restart NetworkManager
	It may be necessary to get the wifi driver
        # dmesg | grep iwlwifi
            iwlwifi 0000:03:00.0: Direct firmware load for iwlwifi-3168-23.ucode failed with error -2
                https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/wireless-products/dual-band-wireless-ac-3168-brief.html
                https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/support/articles/000005511/network-and-i-o/wireless-networking.html
                https://wireless.wiki.kernel.org/_media/en/users/drivers/iwlwifi-3168-ucode-22.361476.0.tgz
                    README, /lib/firmware
                        reboot !
        More about networking on https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Networking/CLI
    7) prepare hotspot - access to both Internet and the device     10.42.0.1
        # journalctl -u NetworkManager.service
        # dnf install dnsmasq

        # nmcli con add type wifi ifname wlp3s0 con-name Hostspot autoconnect yes ssid Hostspot
        # nmcli con modify Hostspot 802-11-wireless.mode ap 802-11-wireless.band bg ipv4.method shared
        # nmcli con modify Hostspot wifi-sec.key-mgmt wpa-psk
        # nmcli con modify Hostspot wifi-sec.psk "password"
        # nmcli connection modify Hostspot connection.autoconnect-priority 1

        # nmcli con up Hostspot
	Note: you may need to "nmcli con down <wifi>" connection before using wifi module as hotspot
    8) prepare the gpio pins
        # dnf install libgpiod libgpiod-devel libgpiod-utils
            Use libgpioinfo, libgpioset, libgpioget to play with the pins. The value on pin will be reset once pin file descriptor released.
                gpioset --mode=time -s 10 -l gpiochip0 55=0
    9) customize login screen message - show IP adresses
	edit /etc/issue
		IP LAN: \4{enp2s0}
		IP WIFI: \4{wlp3s0}
